City-Level Food Waste Prediction & Intelligent Donation Routing

End-to-End Machine Learning + Geospatial Optimization System

Predict surplus food at city zones and intelligently optimize donation routes to NGOs using machine learning, geospatial analytics, and route optimization.

This system analyzes restaurant data, identifies surplus food hotspots, and generates optimized routes to help NGOs collect food efficiently and reduce urban food waste.

Project Overview:

Food wastage is a major urban challenge while many NGOs struggle with inconsistent food supply.

This project builds an intelligent donation logistics system that:

Predicts surplus food generation at restaurant locations

Detects surplus hotspots using geospatial clustering

Matches restaurants with nearby NGOs

Optimizes donation routes using vehicle routing algorithms

Visualizes data through an interactive dashboard

City Focus: Pune, India
Approach: Machine Learning + Geospatial Analytics + Optimization
Impact: Reduced food waste and faster NGO food collection

System Architecture
Real City Data
      ↓
Data Cleaning & Standardization
      ↓
Geospatial Analysis & Hotspot Detection
      ↓
Machine Learning Surplus Prediction
      ↓
Supply–Demand Matching
      ↓
Route Optimization (Vehicle Routing)
      ↓
Interactive Dashboard (Streamlit)

Key Features

Restaurant-level food surplus prediction

Geospatial hotspot detection using clustering

NGO–restaurant matching algorithm

Vehicle Routing Optimization (VRP) using OR-Tools

Interactive Streamlit dashboard

Fully reproducible ML pipeline

Dockerized deployment

Machine Learning Models
Surplus Prediction

XGBoost

LSTM (Time-series forecasting)

Geospatial Analytics

K-Means / DBSCAN clustering

Spatial hotspot detection

Route Optimization

Google OR-Tools Vehicle Routing Problem (VRP)

